ud password</strong>&nbsp;is; there are several approaches to find out. iCloud Reset Password. If you don’t have a reliance on an iOS device close by, you’ll still be able to reset your password by asking for an account recovery. Hence, that is gratifying used while your device has been misplaced or stolen, and you want to sign in to your account even as concurrently denying access to anybody trying to impersonate you. It will take you a few days. But, depending on how a great deal of statistics you supplied to prove your identity.</p><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>&nbsp;Firstly, go to” applied. apple ” id Password reset and then, tap on the Forgot Apple ID or password showing in the middle it centre of the page.</li></ol><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>Now, you’ll be redirected to a new page where you will be required to type your Apple ID or the email address associated with the account.</li><li>&nbsp;Click on Continue, and then do select “I need to reset my password”.</li></ul><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>Now, select the way you feel to reset your password, whether it be through email or by answering a set of security questions. Choose based on your preference.</li><li>If you have selected the email method you’ll see the email has been sent when you see the “Email has been sent” page with a large, green check mark. If you can’t find the email, be sure to check your Spam, Junk, and Trash folders, and if don’t then repeat the steps above to have the email sent again.</li><li>And if you have chosen the security questions method it will require you to confirm some security questions such as your birthday and answer the questions before you’re able to create a new password.</li></ul><h6 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\">Is iCloud password the same as Apple ID password?</h6><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">Yes, they do are the same in terms of the password but there are more things that you should be informed that Your Apple id is the account you use to access Apple services for instance the App save, the iTunes save, Apple Books, Apple track, Face Time, iCloud, iMessage, and more.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">Likewise, iCloud is used to securely save your “images, motion pictures, documents, tune, apps, and more”—and hold them up to date across all of your devices (backup). With iCloud, you can easily share photos, calendars, places, and more with acquaintances. And also Cloud helps to locate the iPhone in case you lose it. Not only to that extent but iCloud also gives you a free email account and 5 GB of storage on your (mail, documents, photographs and videos, and backups) and if that’s 5 GB is not enough you can even buy more storage based on your requirement.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">If the above steps didn’t work so far and you still can’t sign in with your apple id and password then you are advised to contact&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20231001050318/https://teqsman.com/live-chat/apple/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">apple chat support</a>&nbsp;or visit the apple stores near your residence.</p>', 'https://www.teqsman.com/storage/app/public/blog_images/j8rp3iTfDmiKZ0LIVJkahGTo0WvdvHHGgsHJoIjD.webp', NULL, 'reset', 'Ethan Dolan', '2024-09-17 13:28:40', '2024-09-17 13:28:40'),
(278, 'PG&E Shutoff Map: Find and Understand Power Outages', 'pge-shut-off-map', 'PG&E Shutoff Map | Check Power Outages in Your Area', 'Explore this guide on the PG&E shutoff map to understand how the pandemic affected your gas service provider and view current power outages.', 'PG&E Shutoff Map', 'Etah Dolan is a seasoned tech blogger with over 8 years of experience in writing in-depth and engaging articles about the latest trends in technology. Having authored numerous articles on topics ranging from gadgets to software innovations, Etah is passionate about simplifying complex tech concepts for readers. His expertise lies in delivering insightful, easy-to-understand content that resonates with both tech enthusiasts and everyday users.', '<p>Extreme temperatures, drought, and high winds can create conditions that increase the risk of wildfires. To ensure public safety, PG&amp;E may implement a Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) if severe weather threatens the electrical system. This proactive measure helps prevent wildfires. For current shutoff information, check the PG&amp;E shutoff map on their website.</p><h3>How to Prepare for Multiple-Day Outages</h3><p>PG&amp;E offers resources to help you prepare for power outages, minimizing disruption and stress. Visit the Safety Action Center for tips on outage readiness.</p><h3>PG&amp;E Power Shutoff Map</h3><p>As weather conditions in Northern California raise fire risks, PG&amp;E may shut off power in various areas. Use the map below to see where outages are active or being considered. For updated information, PG&amp;E\'s map is refreshed every 15 minutes.</p><h3>Reporting and Receiving Updates</h3><p>To report an outage or get updates, visit PG&amp;E’s website. Real-time outage data and potential shutoff zones are provided by PG&amp;E and updated regularly. For notifications, you can:</p><ul><li><strong>Set Up Alerts</strong>: Log into your PG&amp;E account and configure automatic notifications for outages.</li><li><strong>Get Updates</strong>: Search for specific outages on PG&amp;E’s online map and receive notifications via text, email, or phone.</li></ul><h3>Preparing for Outages</h3><p>To minimize risks and inconveniences:</p><ul><li><strong>Keep Emergency Contacts Handy</strong>: Store important phone numbers for emergencies.</li><li><strong>Backup Plans</strong>: Ensure life support devices have backup power.</li><li><strong>Phone Options</strong>: Use a corded phone if possible.</li><li><strong>Flashlights</strong>: Store flashlights with fresh batteries; avoid candles.</li><li><strong>Turn Off Heat-Generating Devices</strong>: Reduce fire hazards.</li><li><strong>Protect Electronics</strong>: Use surge protectors and unplug devices.</li><li><strong>Food Storage</strong>: Keep the fridge and freezer doors closed; use ice if needed.</li></ul><h3>Conclusion</h3><p>Generators should only be used if properly installed. Improper use can damage property and endanger workers. For more information on safe generator installation, visit PG&amp;E’s safety guidelines.</p>', 'https://www.teqsman.com/storage/app/public/blog_images/3Mqfn2JVG5JU9XMrv5w5MzQQoE6oP1MO9T43HUUF.webp', NULL, 'outage', 'Ethan Dolan', '2024-09-17 13:35:05', '2024-09-17 13:35:05'),
(279, 'Yahoo Mail not working', 'yahoo-not-working', 'Yahoo Mail Not Working iPhone and Android - How to Fix it', 'Many people encounter issues with Yahoo Mail not working from time to time, which can be due to technical problems or other reasons.', 'Yahoo Mail not working', 'Etah Dolan is a seasoned tech blogger with over 8 years of experience in writing in-depth and engaging articles about the latest trends in technology. Having authored numerous articles on topics ranging from gadgets to software innovations, Etah is passionate about simplifying complex tech concepts for readers. His expertise lies in delivering insightful, easy-to-understand content that resonates with both tech enthusiasts and everyday users.', '<p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">It’s aggravating when Yahoo Mail doesn’t work. In an ideal world, there would be a simple way to determine when Yahoo Mail services are down or having issues. Unfortunately, Yahoo mail not working does not provide any system status information for its free mail services</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">In contrast to other web service providers, Yahoo! can be checked to see if it is up and running. The following sequence of steps can help you identify and/or solve problems when&nbsp;<strong>Yahoo! Mail doesn’t work</strong>. Also, check if yahoo SMTP server not working.</p><h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 22px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\">Why Yahoo is not working today?</h2><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">If your&nbsp;<em>Yahoo mail not working today</em>, there may be an outage issue. Search for tweets from @<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20231001055914/https://twitter.com/yahoomail\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">YahooMail</a>, @<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20231001055914/https://twitter.com/YahooCare\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">YahooCare</a>, or even the main account of @Yahoo on Twitter. Although rare, a tweet from one of these accounts would serve as official confirmation that Yahoo! The mail service is having problems.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Check updates on Social Media</strong></p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">You can also use a quick search on Twitter to find out if other people are having trouble connecting to Yahoo! Mail. Search for terms like Yahoo! Mail, Yahoo Mail, or #yahoomail. Follow the links to each of these terms to see the latest Twitter search results for each article. If you see several recent tweets from people who have problems with Yahoo! Email, any problem you’re experiencing is likely to affect many accounts, not just yours. You can also see if yahoo business emails not working.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Check third-party status services</strong>&nbsp;to see if other websites cannot access Yahoo Mail. To test whether the https://isup.me service can connect to Yahoo Mail, open your browser and type mail.yahoo.com. https://downdetector.com/status/yahoo-mail is a status page on which connection and failure problems for Yahoo Mail are tracked and reported. At all times, you should expect at least some issues to be reported. However, if you find hundreds or thousands of identified issues, the issue is almost certainly out of your control. There could also be a yahoo mail, not loading problem.</p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 21px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\">How to fix yahoo mail not working</h3><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">If any of these status services report a problem, you can stop troubleshooting. The Yahoo Mail team has to solve the problem.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">If no problems are reported with these tools, it is time to troubleshoot your setup.</p><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li><strong>Turn off your device</strong>, waits a minute, and then turns it on again. Restarting a system often fixes various app, storage, and/or connection problems. Restarting laptops and desktops often also resolves temporary application issues. On mobile devices, restarting allows your device to restore network connections.</li><li><strong>Open a web browser on your device&nbsp;</strong>to see if you can connect to other websites like google.com. If you cannot connect to the Internet, there may be a network connection problem.</li><li><strong>If you’re using a laptop, tablet, or phone, you may be trying to connect to another network.</strong>&nbsp;For example, try connecting to another nearby Wi-Fi network, e.g. B. in a local library, cafe, or at work. If your device has a cellular connection, e.g. for example, a Smartphone, turn off Wi-Fi so that your device connects to your carrier’s network instead. Try connecting to Yahoo! Mail again after changing networks.</li><li><strong>Try another way to connect to Yahoo Mail</strong>. If you normally use an app to access Yahoo! Mail, try a browser. Or if you’re normally a Yahoo! Email with a browser, try another browser. You can install and try Chrome, Firefox, or Brave to get on Yahoo! Mail. Switch to Safari on macOS and iOS systems, or Edge on Windows, iOS, or Android systems, if you generally use one of these three browsers.</li><li>Download and install one of the above browsers on your device, then open it and navigate to https://mail.yahoo.com to log in.</li><li><strong>If you’re using an Android, iPhone, or iPad device</strong>, you can install the Yahoo Mail app to connect directly to Yahoo Mail. In contrast to mobile mail apps, where some settings or configuration adjustments may have to be made, the Yahoo mobile app is intended to explicitly allow access to Yahoo Mail on your mobile device. Install either Yahoo Mail for Android or Yahoo Mail for iOS, and then log in to your account.</li><li><strong>If you have access to another device connected to the Internet</strong>, try accessing your Yahoo! Mail on this device. For example, if you’re having trouble accessing Yahoo Mail on a desktop computer, switch to a laptop, tablet, or Smartphone instead. Go to https://mail.yahoo.com on this other device and log in to your account.</li><li><strong>If the system does not accept</strong>&nbsp;your account name and/or password, start the password recovery process.</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">On the Yahoo Mail login page, tap or click “Problems signing in?” Shortcut. Enter one of four pieces of information on this page to begin the recovery process:</p><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>You must have an yahoo e-mail address.</li><li>Your mobile phone number.</li><li>A recovery email address.</li><li>A recovery phone number.&nbsp;</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">Follow the instructions that vary depending on the recovery method and the information you provided. Search on Google my yahoo mail is not working.</p><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\">Yahoo Mail not working on iPhone, iPad</h4><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Uninstall and reinstall Yahoo Mail on iPhone, iPad</strong></p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">The behavior of your Yahoo mail is completely wrong and you cannot find your settings after updating apps or you can log out and log into your Yahoo account. People who cannot find the notification settings on the iPhone / iPad cannot create the account key on their Yahoo Mail or set up the iOS app. Account key push notifications will not appear in your iPhone notification center. Delete your Yahoo Mail app.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">On the iPhone home screen, find Yahoo Mail app, touch and hold the app icon&gt; Until 3D popup appears&gt; Find options&nbsp;<strong>Delete</strong>&nbsp;<strong>app</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Confirm</strong>&nbsp;delete. Now reinstall from the iPhone App Store,</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>1. Delete the app and reinstall Yahoo Mail on iPhone</strong></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>Open the&nbsp;<strong>App Store</strong>&gt; Tap the&nbsp;<strong>search icon</strong>&gt; Enter&nbsp;<strong>Yahoo Mail&gt;</strong>&nbsp;Download the app on your iPhone / iPad.</li><li>That’s it. You will need to log in to the Yahoo Mail account again after reinstallation.</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>2. Update the Yahoo Mail app on iPhone</strong></p><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li>If iPhone’s default email app doesn’t work, you should download a separate Yahoo application available from the App Store. If you don’t want to opt for a Yahoo application, wait for Apple to respond to your request.</li></ul><h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 19px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\"><strong>Yahoo mail not working on android</strong></h5><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">Since Yahoo Mail is a free web-based email application, you may be familiar with it. The user can also access other web-based apps and services through this email service. Besides, the developers have even introduced various functions into the Yahoo app that have made it easier to send emails. However, many users still have problems with the Yahoo Mail app when accessing an Android device. Fortunately, this problem can be easily resolved by contacting Help or by following some of the solutions provided in this part of the article.</p><h6 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Cambria;\"><strong>3 ways to fix Yahoo does not work with Android problem</strong></h6><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><li><strong>Solve network problems</strong>: The most common reason why Yahoo Mail doesn’t work is network problems. To fix this problem, users are advised to check the network settings properly. The user can also check whether the app authorization is activated correctly.</li><li><strong>Sign-in Issues</strong>: Another reason Yahoo doesn’t answer the problem can be the significant issues that can be resolved by following a few simple steps. There is a possibility that this problem occurs due to the old phone number added to the account. Simply open your account and add the new phone number under Security Settings and click Send Code. Then enter that particular code and you’ll get access to your Yahoo account after verification.</li><li><strong>The outdated version of the app</strong>: There is a possibility that some users may encounter a problem with Yahoo Mail that is not working due to the outdated version of the app. We, therefore, recommend that users simply start the Google Play Store and select the Yahoo app in the installed apps area.</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">Also, click the update option to update the Yahoo app. So these were the few solutions you can try to fix the problem that Yahoo is not responding. Also, the user can try contacting Yahoo Support for assistance to resolve this issue quickly and promptly.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Cambria; font-size: 18px;\">If you cannot access your Yahoo Mail account using any of the above methods, you may need to contact&nbsp;Yahoo live chat&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20231001055914/https://teqsman.com/mail/yahoo-quick-fix-tool/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">Yahoo mail quick fix tool</a>&nbsp;for help.</p>', 'https://www.teqsman.com/storage/app/public/blog_images/EXuCCGYNh2XByrhDC4a2Uw4VPRRlR9Ka3cNJNOXE.jpg', NULL, 'mail', 'Ethan Dolan', '2024-11-19 10:15:25', '2024-09-17 13:38:28'),
(280, 'Comcast outage map guide is hare', 'comcast-internet', 'Comcast Outage Map | Xfinity Internet Issue Fixes Guide', 'As with the Comcast outage map last month, which lasted nearly 48 hours, you can read our Comcast Xfinity internet down blog post.', 'Comcast Outage Map, Comcast internet Outage Map', 'Meenu is a seasoned tech blogger with over 4 years of experience in writing in-depth and engaging articles about the latest trends in technology. Having authored numerous articles on topics ranging from gadgets to software innovations, Etah is passionate about simplifying complex tech concepts for readers. His expertise lies in delivering insightful, easy-to-understand content that resonates with both tech enthusiasts and everyday users.', '<p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">Comcast is an American telecommunications company that provides cable TV, internet, telephone, and wireless services to the consumer under the Xfinity brand. Generally, these offerings are available in triple-play packages.&nbsp;Comcast&nbsp;is the biggest cable TV company and largest home Internet service provider in the US. How to fix Xfinity Comcast outage map issues.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">There are several reasons for Xfinity internet issues. In fact, any Internet service provider may occasionally experience service interruptions or deliver services that fall short of quality standards. Since there’re many users at any given moment, there’re chances of network overload. While the network of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20230325105330/https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comcast\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">Comcast</a>&nbsp;is built to handle large loads, sometimes the servers do feel disabled under heavy usage.</p><h2 style=\"font-size: 22px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">How do I fix my Comcast Internet outage?</h2><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>If your Comcast Xfinity Internet connection appears to be working properly, you can try the following</strong>:-</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">If you’re encountering Xfinity internet issues, it could be a problem with your modem or a general outage in your locality. You can restart your modem and see if the issue is fixed. However, if there’s a local Comcast outage, you can go to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20230325105330/http://teqsman.com/bill-pay/comcast/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"color: rgb(84, 190, 115);\">Comcast bill pay</a>&nbsp;and check the estimated resolution time.</p><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>The most common step you must try is to reset your router, restart your smartphone/pc.</li><li>Move near to the Wi-Fi router/hotspot.</li><li>Check for Wi-Fi interference using a Wi-Fi analyzer app. If so, move your router in a different place or set a fixed channel for your Wi-Fi from your router admin interface.</li><li>Update your Wi-Fi router firmware and Wi-Fi adapter drivers and by checking the manufacturers’ websites.</li><li>If on a public Wi-Fi network, connect to another one; that may very well simply be a bad Wi-Fi hotspot.</li></ol><h3 style=\"font-size: 21px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">How do I know if Comcast is an outage or down?</h3><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">If one or more of your Xfinity services isn’t working, you can check to see if there’s a service outage or down:</p><h4 style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">Comcast Outage Map</h4><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>You can also look the Comcast Outage Map in My Account:</strong></p><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>As a first step, you must log into your account.</li><li>Then click the Services tab at the top of the page.</li><li>Click on the Status Center link to view the current status.</li><li>Next, click or choose the Outage map icon.</li><li>Service status and outages in your immediate or surrounding area will be displayed on the map.</li></ol><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">You can only look at your service address. You can’t look at any other customers’ statuses, and they can’t view yours.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>My Account</strong></p><h5 style=\"font-size: 19px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">To check for an outage in My Comcast Account:</h5><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>First of all, Sign in to My Account and click the Services tab.</li><li>Then click the Status Centre link.</li><li>You will be informed via a personalised banner message.</li><li>Whether or not you are experiencing an outage.</li><li>The type of probable outage.</li><li>The approximate time when the outage will be fixed (if available).</li><li>If there’s an outage that only influences 1 service, that service will show a red status. This means they’re already aware of the outage and working to fix it, so there’s no requirement to contact them.</li><li>If all services show a green status, there’re no reported outages in your locality. If you’re having problems with your services but there isn’t an outage, you can try troubleshooting then.</li><li>If troubleshooting doesn’t work, you may need to report your issue(s) using the Xfinity Status Center so we can assist determine what’s causing it and offer you more data.</li></ol><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">Note: You can also check for outages using the Xfinity My Account app on your mobile phone. Once you log in, a banner appears immediately if you’re impacted by an outage. Simply tap it to get more info.</p><h5 style=\"font-size: 19px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">Comcast Outage Text Message Alerts</h5><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">If you’ve registered your contact number for Comcast Alerts, you can text OUT to 266278 (COMCAST) to check for outages in your locality. The use of data and messaging may be subject to additional charges. As soon as your Xfinity services are restored, you can opt to receive a text message.</p><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>Sign in to Xfinity account first.</li><li>Click the Services tab then click the Status Center link.</li><li>If you’re experiencing an outage, a banner will appear on the top of the Status Center and Outage Map pages.</li><li>Click Text me when it’s resolved.</li><li>Type your contact number and choose to get a Text.</li><li>You’ll get a confirmation message that allows you know you are signed up to receive a text message update when your services are restored.</li></ol><h6 style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>Why Comcast Xfinity Internet Service Goes Out</strong></h6><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">Home users are not the only ones affected by Comcast outages and ‘blackouts’. As a result, they can cause problems across an entire state or country. Whether you are a large scale data centre or a modest home user, you are not safe from internet outages.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>This occurs most often when:</strong></p><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>There’s a problem with Comcast’s Internet infrastructure;</li><li>The network is overloaded, especially Wi-Fi. This occurs in busy places such as the street, stadiums, and concerts.</li><li>You use a faulty Xfinity Wi-Fi hotspot.</li><li>Sometimes your Internet may be disconnecting because of reasons that are particular to your connection only, such as:</li><li>A defective cable from your modem/router to your pc.</li><li>Wi-Fi hotspot strength is poor – you may be close to the edge of the Wi-Fi network.</li><li>Wireless interference with other Wi-Fi hotspots or close devices.</li><li>Network adapter drivers are out of date or the modem/router firmware is out of date.</li></ol><h6 style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">What causes Comcast outages?</h6><ol type=\"1\" style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>Speed fluctuation from Internet providers can be caused by a blockage; however, sometimes the lines from your provider aren’t as optimized as they must be. You may be paying for a particular rate, but receiving a slower rate of service, which can simply cause service interruptions.</li><li>When the link between the device and the server is interrupted and cannot connect it occurs due to the failed link to your service provider. Often, failed links to your service provider can be caused by storms, downed wires, or even animals.</li><li>One of the common issues is network blockage is caused when there’re several people trying to access a network at one time, in a certain locality. During this time, your circuit quality may gridlock or worsen. It is the simplest kind of internet outage to solve while also being the most stoppable.</li></ol>', 'https://www.teqsman.com/storage/app/public/blog_images/EXuCCGYNh2XByrhDC4a2Uw4VPRRlR9Ka3cNJNOXE.jpg', NULL, 'outage', 'Meenu', '2024-11-19 10:15:18', '2024-11-02 13:46:28'),
(281, 'Charter bill pay', 'charter', 'Charter Bill Pay Explained: Everything You Need to Know', 'Need charter bill pay number to Payment your bill? Here is the detailed guide on what to do. Try this information or call on phone.', 'Charter Bill Pay', 'Meenu is a seasoned tech blogger with over 4 years of experience in writing in-depth and engaging articles about the latest trends in technology. Having authored numerous articles on topics ranging from gadgets to software innovations, Etah is passionate about simplifying complex tech concepts for readers. His expertise lies in delivering insightful, easy-to-understand content that resonates with both tech enthusiasts and everyday users.', '<p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">Customers can submit their Charter bills around the clock in the white Dropbox in front of the community center on 5151 Marsh Road. Place your check with your payment tube in a sealed envelope. How to contact&nbsp;<strong>Charter bill pay</strong>&nbsp;customer care executive. You can use our automated service to pay your bill over the phone.</p><h2 style=\"font-size: 22px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">Charter bill payments online using:</h2><ul style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><li>Checking or savings account</li><li>A debit card or MasterCard, Visa, American Express, or Discover credit card.</li></ul><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>If you choose to make your payment by phone with the assistance of a customer service agent, you’ll be charged a $5.00 processing fee.</p><h3 style=\"font-size: 21px; color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Assistant;\">Charter bill payment:</h3><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assistant;\">Charter bill payments can also be made in person at the Treasurer’s office between 8:00 a.m. and 5:00 p.m. daily in the community center.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(86, 86, 86); font-family: Assis